AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Bank is a unique identifier of a Bank for this Organization or for a Business Partner with whom this Organization transacts.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Bank Account
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A monetary account of funds held in a recognized banking institution.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Bank Account identifies an account at this Bank.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Partner Bank Account
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Bank Account of the Business Partner
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Partner Bank Account identifies the bank account to be used for this Business Partner

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Withholding
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Withholding
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Withholding indicates the type of withholding to be calculated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Account No.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Account Number
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Account Number indicates the Number assigned to this account

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Beneficiary
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Business Partner to whom payment is made
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Beneficiary indicates the Business Partner to whom payment will be made. This field is only displayed if the Paid to Third Party checkbox is selected.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Charge Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount of a cost or expense incurred during business activity.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Charge Amount indicates the amount for an additional charge.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Classification
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The Classification can be used to optionally group products.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Classification can be used to optionally group products.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Limit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Amount of Credit allowed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Credit Limit field indicates the credit limit for this account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Current Balance
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Current Balance
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Current Balance field indicates the current balance in this account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Direct shipment
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Ship direct from Vendor to Customer
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Direct Shipment indicates if this line will ship directly from the vendor to the customer

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Category
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A classification of document types that are shown and processed in the same window.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Base Type identifies the base or starting point for a document. Multiple document types may share a single document base type.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Number of Copies
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The number of copies of each document that will be printed.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Copies indicates the number of copies of each document that will be generated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Comments
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Note is used for recording any additional information regarding this product.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Email
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An email address for a specified business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Email Address is the Electronic Mail ID for this User and should be fully qualified (e.g. joe.smith@company.com).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Enforce Price Limit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Do not allow prices below the limit price
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Enforce Price Limit check box indicates that prices cannot be below the limit price in Orders. Invoices are not checked.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Exempt Reason
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Reason for not withholding
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Exempt Reason indicates the reason that monies are not withheld from this employee.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fix Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Fix amounted amount to be levied or paid
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fixed Amount indicates a fixed amount to be levied or paid.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Last Day Cut-off
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Last day to include for next due date
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Last Day Cut-off indicates the last day invoices can have to be included in the current due date.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Maturity Date 1
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The day of the month that invoices are due. 3 maturity dates can be defined.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fix Month Day indicates the day of the month that invoices are due. This field is displayed only when the fixed due date checkbox is selected. 3 different fix month days can be defined.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Offset Month Due
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Number of months (0=same, 1=following)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Offset Month Due indicates the number of months from the current month to indicate an invoice is due. A 0 indicates the same month, a 1 the following month.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoicing Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates that this address is the Invoicing Address
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Invoicing Address checkbox indicates if this location is the Invoicing Address for this Business Partner

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fixed Due Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Payment is due on a fixed date
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fixed Due Date checkbox indicates if invoices using this payment term will be due on a fixed day of the month.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Foreign Currency Account
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Balances in foreign currency accounts are held in the nominated currency
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Balances in foreign currency accounts are held in the nominated currency and translated to functional currency

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Mandatory Withholding
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Monies must be withheld
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Mandatory Withholding checkbox indicates that monies must be withheld from this employee.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Own Bank
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Bank for this Organization
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Own Bank field indicates if this bank is for this Organization as opposed to a Bank for a Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Payment to External Party
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Amount paid to someone other than the Business Partner
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Paid to Third Party checkbox indicates that the amounts are paid to someone other than the Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Pay from Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Business Partner pays from that address and we'll send dunning letters there
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Pay From Address checkbox indicates if this location is the address the Business Partner pays from.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Withholding Percentage
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Withholding amount is a percentage of the invoice amount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Percent Withholding checkbox indicates if the withholding amount is a percentage of the invoice amount.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Remit to Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Address we send payments to
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Remit to Address checkbox indicates if this location is the address to which we should send payments to this Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Same Tax
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Use the same tax as the main transaction
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Same Tax checkbox indicates that this charge should use the same tax as the main transaction.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Shipping Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Business Partner address to ship goods to
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Shipping Address checkbox indicates if this location is the address to use when shipping orders to this Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tax Exempt
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A condition stating that for a specific case, taxes must not be applied.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If a business partner is exempt from tax, the exempt tax rate is used. For this, you need to set up a tax rate with a 0% rate and indicate that this is your tax exempt rate. This is required for tax reporting, so that you can track tax exempt transactions.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Prorate Tax
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Tax is Prorated
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Prorate Tax checkbox indicates if this tax is prorated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tax Withholding
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This is a tax related withholding
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Tax Withholding checkbox indicates if this withholding is tax related.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Temporarily Exempt
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Temporarily do not withhold taxes
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Temporary Exempt checkbox indicates that for a limited time, taxes will not be withheld for this employee.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Max. Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Maximum Amount in invoice currency
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Maximum Amount indicates the maximum amount in invoice currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Min. Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Minimum Amount in invoice currency
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Minimum amount indicates the minimum amount as stated in the currency of the invoice.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Minimum Order Qty.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The minimum number of an item that must be purchased at one time from a vendor.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Minimum Order Quantity indicates the smallest quantity of this product which can be ordered.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Quantity per Package
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The number of a specific item that comes in one package.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Order Pack Quantity indicates the number of units in each pack of this product.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: PO Form of Payment
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The method used to pay the request.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Payment Rule indicates the method of purchase payment.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Percent
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Withholding percentage
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Percent indicates the percentage used for withholding.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Order Reference
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A reference or document order number as listed in business partner application.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This can be used to input a reference for this specific transaction. For example, a Purchase Order number can be input on a Sales Order for easier reference.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Last Purchase Price
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The last price pad for this product, as noted in a completed purchase order.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Last PO Price indicates the last price paid (per the purchase order) for this product.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Price Limit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The lowest net price a specified item may be sold for.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Net Price Limit indicates the lowest price for a product stated in the Price List Currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Unit Price
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The regular or normal price of a product in the respective price list.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Standard Price indicates the standard or normal price for a product on this price list. This price might be net or gross depending on its price list configuration.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: SO Sub Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Sales Order Sub Type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
The SO Sub Type indicates the type of sales order this document refers to. This field only appears when the Document Base Type is Sales Order. The selection made here will determine which documents will be generated when an order is processed and which documents must be generated manually or in batches.
The following outlines this process.
SO Sub Type of Standard Order will generate just the Order document when the order is processed.
The Delivery Note, Invoice and Receipt must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of Warehouse Order will generate the Order and Delivery Note.
The Invoice and Receipt must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of Credit Order will generate the Order, Delivery Note and Invoice.
The Reciept must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of POS (Point of Sale) will generate all document

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Logic 2
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Default value hierarchy, separated by ;
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The defaults are evaluated in the order of definition, the first not null value becomes the default value of the column. The values are separated by comma or semicolon. a) Literals:. 'Text' or 123 b) Variables - in format @Variable@ - Login e.g. #Date, #AD_Org_ID, #AD_Client_ID - Accounting Schema: e.g. $C_AcctSchema_ID, $C_Calendar_ID - Global defaults: e.g. DateFormat - Window values (all Picks, CheckBoxes, RadioButtons, and DateDoc/DateAcct) c) SQL code with the tag: @SQL=SELECT something AS DefaultValue FROM ... The SQL statement can contain variables. There can be no other value other than the SQL statement. The default is only evaluated, if no user preference is defined. Default definitions are ignored for record columns as Key, Parent, Client as well as Buttons.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Product Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An important classification used to determine the accounting and management of a product.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: There are four types of products available. Item type can be used to configure any product such as raw materials or finished products ready to be sold. An item can be flagged as Socked or not, can be part of a production process and/or can be a bill of materials. Item type is the only one for which a cost type calculation can be configured. Service type can be used to configure consultancy, transport or insurance services. Service type can be purchased or sold but can not be stocked. A service can be a bill of materials. Finally Resource and Expense are product types which can be used to distinguish between different types of products which can be purchased or sold but make not sense to stock. Expense type can be used to configure travel expenses fto be used while reporting Employee Expenses. The fact of using a given product type does not mean a different accounting. All product types account same way while being purchased, stocked or sold. All of them use the ledger accounts defined in the Accounting tab of the Product window.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Grouping
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
For scheduled invoicing, break into different invoices if the related values are different. The value is used as a binary code with 15 digits: 1.-Order organization (AD_Org_ID) 2.-Order (C_Order_ID) 3.-Shipment (M_InOut_ID) 4.-Invoice location (BillTo_ID) 5.-Ship location (C_BPartner_Location_ID) 6.-Sales representative (SalesRep_ID) 7.-Payment rule (PaymentRule) 8.-Payment term (C_PaymentTerm_ID) 9.-Currency (C_Currency_ID) 10.-Campaign (C_Campaign_ID) 11.-Project (C_Project_ID) 12.-Activity (C_Activity_ID) 13.-Transaction organization (AD_OrgTrx_ID) 14.-User defined 1 (User1) 15.-User defined 2 (User2)
For example, if you want to create different invoices for each ship location for a customer, use the value "By ship location" (000010000000000)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: IBAN
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: International standard for identifying bank accounts across national borders
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Code that identifies uniquely one bank account, no matter the country it belongs to. It consists of a ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code, followed by two check digits, and up to thirty alphanumeric characters for the domestic bank account number, called the BBAN (Basic Bank Account Number). It is up to each country's national banking community to decide on the length of the BBAN for accounts in that country, but its length must be fixed for any given country.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: IBAN Code
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Country Code asigned to a country in the IBAN structure.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: IBAN Length
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The length of the IBAN code of a bank account is variable, depending on the country.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Then International Bank Account Number structure do not stablish a specific length: it depends on the country. This field will define the length of the IBAN codes for that country.

Indicates whether the report is a "Point in Time" or a "Periodic" report.
A Point in Time report is obtained as of a given date, taking into account the whole historical financial movements; an example of point in time report is the Balance Sheet.
A periodic report is executed for a date range and it does not carry forward the balance of accounting movements previous to the range; an example of periodic report is the Income Statement.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Dependency Enforcement
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Dependency enforcement defines which are the versions of the dependent module that are compatible with the parent one.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
Dependency enforcement defines which are the versions of the dependent module that are compatible with the parent one.
The values it can contain are:
*Major Version (default). The compatible versions are all the minor version within the same major version. If "Last Version" is defined being a different major version than "From Version", "Last Version" defines the highest compatible minor version; if "Last Version" is in the same major version than "From Version" this value is not taken into account. It is the default value. *Minor Version. Defines a strict dependency to the exact minor version. In case no "Last Version" is set, "From Version" is the only compatible version. Other case the compatible versions are all between "From" and "Last Version" values. *None. "From Version" is the only field taken into account, there is no restriction on different major versions.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: User Editable Enforcement
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines whether the enforcement can be overwritten by user
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When a dependency/inclusion is "User Editable Enforcement", the enforcement defined for that dependency can be overwritten at instance level.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Instance Enforcement

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In case the dependency is set as "User Editable", this value overwrites the Instance Enforcement one.

When processes are executed from a button in a window, by default, they inherit permissions granted to the window. So if the window is accessible it can be executed without the need of explicitly granting access for that role to the process.

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A more descriptive identifier (that does need to be unique) of a record/document that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter). It is up to 60 characters in length.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Saturday
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Allows to apply the discount on Saturdays

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: HQL Filter Clause
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: By using this HQL clause, initially the user will not be able to see data that does not fit the criteria. Once the user clears the filter, this hql clause will not be applied.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: By using this HQL clause, initially the user will not be able to see data that does not fit the criteria. Once the user clears the filter, this hql clause will not be applied.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Summed Line Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The final sum of all line totals made to a specified document or transaction (not including taxes).
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Total amount displays the total of all lines in document currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Cron Expression
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Cron expression defining when and how often a trigger should be triggered.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Cron expression defining when and how often a trigger should be triggered.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Data Origin
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Field to specify the type of data origin: physical table/view or datasource
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Field to specify the type of data origin: physical table/view or datasource

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: On Hold
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This flag allows to block the customer. By checking it, a new section will be shown called Business Partner Blocking with the possible blocking options.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This flag allows to block the customer. By checking it, a new section will be shown called Business Partner Blocking with the possible blocking options.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting entry Description
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Description of the accounting entry
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Description of the accounting entry

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Update Payment Plan
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Shows a popup where the user can modify some payment plan details.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Shows a popup where the user can modify some payment plan details.
AD_ELEMENT.PO_DESCRIPTION: Shows a popup where the user can modify some payment plan details.
AD_ELEMENT.PO_HELP: Shows a popup where the user can modify some payment plan details.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Upon Receipt Use
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Account used upon receipt
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Account used upon receipt

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: General Accounts
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Accounts being used for general purposes such as income statement account, error and balance handling accounts.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: General purpose accounts can be defined here for the General Ledger. This window as well holds additional configuration related to fiscal year closing.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Enable Bank Statement
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Enable Bank Statement Accounting
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This flag enables accounting for Bank Statements. Some accounts will be required for proper configuration

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sms
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This field defines the default value for the Via SMS check in Web POS Customer Creation
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This field defines the default value for the Via SMS check in Web POS Customer Creation

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Gross Unit Price
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Price inclusive of taxes
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This is the price that is provided when the price is inclusive of taxes.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Calendar Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Calendar name identifier.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Calendar name identifier.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: API Key
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Identifier of a concrete property into the external system
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Identifier of a concrete property into the external system

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Period
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Used for the different calculation methods of default period in a deferred revenue/expense plan.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tree Structure
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Inner structure of the tree
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Three different tree structures are available: - AD Tree Node: The information regarding the hierarchy of the data is stored in the ADTree and ADTreeNode tables. - Link to Parent in Table: This structure can be used when the informartion regarding the hierarchy of the data can be fetched from the own table. In this case, there has to be a column in the table that points to the row that represents the parent node of the record. - Custom: For other tree tables, a manual datasource can be defined

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Max not reserved stock
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Max Qty of the product in stock, not reserved.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Max Qty of the product in stock, not reserved. When running purchasing plan to suggest needed purchase orders to fullfill the pending sales orders and safety stock, it will buy enough to leave as well the stock in this Max Qty.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Reference Date
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The date used as a Reference for the document

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Cost Adjustment
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Represents a Cost Adjustment header where costs of some transactions are adjusted.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Source Process
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Identifies the Process type that generated the Cost Adjustment

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Cost Adjustment Line
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A Cost Adjustment Line is a Material Transaction whose cost needs to be adjusted by the amount defined.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Is Source
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Identifies the transactions that required the adjustment.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Needs Posting
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Determines whether the adjustment line amount needs to be posted to the ledger or not.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Adjustment Amount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Is the amount that needs to be added to the Cost Amount of the transaction.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Show Tree Node Icons
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: It defines if the tree nodes icons should be shown
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: It defines if the tree nodes icons (folder and leaf) should be shown. It only applies if the tree grid is in read only mode.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fix Backdated Transactions
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Fix Backdated Transactions process
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Process that recalculates costs of backdated transactions until the given date. Run process from Costing Rules window.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Alert Status
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Status of the alert: New: The alert has been created and has not been reviewed yet. Read: The alert has been reviewed and user is waiting to be solved. Solved: The alert has been solved and is not an issue any more. Exception: The alert has been acknowledged but not action is going to be made to solve it.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Memo
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Credit Memo checkbox only applies to Invoice document types. Invoices marked as Credit Memo will behave as Credit Memos, which implies that: "Total gross amount" must always be positive. "Payment Plan" will be negative.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Credit Memo checkbox only applies to Invoice document types. Invoices marked as Credit Memo will behave as Credit Memos, which implies that: - "Total gross amount" must always be positive. - "Payment Plan" will be negative. - Accounting will be opposite than Invoice accounting.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Base Net Unit Price
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
Net unit price before applying this promotion. In case multiple promotions are applied in cascade, this price is the one after applying all promotions with more priority than current one.
This field is populated in case the used price list does not include taxes.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Run Time
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Operation run time
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Operation run time
